main event: Mrs. Jane Doe observed a brightly lit object in the sky moving in a southerly direction on June 6, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared oval in shape and bright white in color., Mrs. Doe estimated the object to be about 1000 feet in altitude., The object moved rapidly and silently., The sighting was reported at clear skies with stars visible., No other witnesses reported the sighting.
sighted object: brightly lit object in the sky
